Acarbose.name: Acarbose
Acarbose.description: Acarbose is a medication used to treat type 2 diabetes. It works by inhibiting alpha-glucosidase, an enzyme responsible for breaking down complex carbohydrates into glucose in the small intestine.

Acetaminophen.name: Acetaminophen
Acetaminophen.description: Acetaminophen, also known as paracetamol or by the brand name Tylenol, is an analgesic and antipyretic.

Acetazolamide.name: Acetazolamide
Acetazolamide.description: Acetazolamide is a first generation carbonic anhydrase inhibitor used to treat glaucoma, epilepsy, altitude sickness, and heart failure related edema.

Acitretin.name: Acitretin
Acitretin.description: Acitretin is a second-generation oral retinoid used in the treatment of severe resistant psoriasis. Because of the potential for problems and severe side effects it is generally used in only very severe cases that have been unresponsive to other treatments.

Adalimumab.name: Adalimumab
Adalimumab.description: Used to treat autoimmune conditions such as rheumatoid arthritis, Crohn's disease, and psoriasis by targeting TNF-alpha.

Adapalene.name: Adapalene
Adapalene.description: Adapalene is a third-generation topical retinoid primarily used in the treatment of mild-moderate acne, and is also used off-label to treat keratosis pilaris.

Albuterol.name: Albuterol
Albuterol.description: Albuterol, also known as Salbutamol, is a short-acting, selective beta2-adrenergic receptor agonist used to treat asthma and COPD.

Amphotericin B.name: Amphotericin B
Amphotericin B.description: Amphotericin B is an antifungal medication used for fungal infections and leishmaniasis.

Aripiprazole.name: Aripiprazole
Aripiprazole.description: Aripiprazole is an atypical antipsychotic used in the treatment of psychiatric disorders.

Atenolol.name: Atenolol
Atenolol.description: Atenolol is a selective beta-1 blocker used to treat hypertension and angina.

Atomoxetine.name: Atomoxetine
Atomoxetine.description: Atomoxetine is a selective norepinephrine reuptake inhibitor (SNRI) used in the management of attention deficit hyperactivity disorder (ADHD).

Atorvastatin.name: Atorvastatin
Atorvastatin.description: Atorvastatin is a cholesterol-lowering HMG-CoA reductase inhibitor used to reduce risk of cardiovascular disease.

Atovaquone; proguanil.name: Atovaquone; proguanil
Atovaquone; proguanil.description: Atovaquone/proguanil, sold under the brand name Malarone among others, is a fixed-dose combination medication used to treat and prevent malaria, including chloroquine-resistant malaria.

Auranofin.name: Auranofin
Auranofin.description: Auranofin is a gold salt used to treat rheumatoid arthritis sold under the brand name Ridaura.

Azelastine.name: Azelastine
Azelastine.description: Azelastine is a histamine H1-receptor antagonist used intranasally to treat allergic and vasomotor rhinitis and in an ophthalmic solution to treat allergic conjunctivitis.

Azithromycin.name: Azithromycin
Azithromycin.descrption: Azithromycin is a macrolide antibiotic used to treat bacterial infections.

Benazepril.name: Benazepril
Benazepril.description: Benazepril is an ACE inhibitor used to treat hypertension.

Bevacizumab.name: Bevacizumab
Bevacizumab.description: Used in cancer therapy for conditions like colorectal and lung cancer by inhibiting vascular endothelial growth factor (VEGF).

Chlorpromazine.name: Chlorpromazine
Chlorpromazine.description: Chlorpromazine is an antipsychotic medication used to treat schizophrenia and bipolar disorder.

Dextroamphetamine; Dextroamphetamine Sac.name: Dextroamphetamine; Dextroamphetamine Saccharate; Amphetamine; Amphetamine Aspartate

clincalc.name: Dextroamphetamine; Dextroamphetamine Saccharate; Amphetamine; Amphetamine Aspartate

Dolutegravir; lamivudine.name: Dolutegravir; lamivudine
Dolutegravir; lamivudine.description: Dolutegravir/lamivudine, sold under the brand name Dovato, is a fixed-dose combination antiretroviral medication for the treatment of HIV/AIDS.

Dupilumab.name: Dupilumab
Dupilumab.description: Treats moderate-to-severe atopic dermatitis, asthma, and chronic rhinosinusitis by targeting IL-4 and IL-13 receptors.

Infliximab.name: Infliximab
Infliximab.description: Used for autoimmune diseases such as Crohn's disease, ulcerative colitis, and rheumatoid arthritis by inhibiting TNF-alpha.

Nivolumab.name: Nivolumab
Nivolumab.description: A PD-1 checkpoint inhibitor used to treat cancers like melanoma, non-small cell lung cancer, and renal cell carcinoma.

Omalizumab.name: Omalizumab
Omalizumab.description: Treats allergic asthma and chronic idiopathic urticaria by targeting IgE to reduce allergic response.

Pancrelipase Amylase; Pancrelipase Lipas.name: Pancrelipase Amylase; Pancrelipase Lipase; Pancrelipase Protease

clincalc.name: Pancrelipase Amylase; Pancrelipase Lipase; Pancrelipase Protease

Pembrolizumab.name: Pembrolizumab
Pembrolizumab.description: An immune checkpoint inhibitor used to treat various cancers, including melanoma and lung cancer, by targeting PD-1.

Rituximab.name: Rituximab
Rituximab.description: Treats conditions like non-Hodgkin's lymphoma, chronic lymphocytic leukemia, and rheumatoid arthritis by targeting CD20 on B cells.

Secukinumab.name: Secukinumab
Secukinumab.description: Used to treat plaque psoriasis, ankylosing spondylitis, and psoriatic arthritis by targeting IL-17A.

Trastuzumab.name: Trastuzumab
Trastuzumab.description: Used to treat HER2-positive breast cancer and gastric cancer by targeting the HER2 receptor.

Xylometazoline.name: Xylometazoline
Xylometazoline.description: Xylometazoline is a direct-acting alpha-adrenergic agonist used for the treatment of nasal congestion.

Zanamivir.name: Zanamivir
Zanamivir.description: Zanamivir is a neuraminidase inhibitor used to treat influenza A and B.

Ziprasidone.name: Ziprasidone
Ziprasidone: Ziprasidone is an atypical antipsychotic used to manage schizophrenia and bipolar mania
